CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 2, 1954, pg. 2, reads: "It'll be Boring on 'Deep Wylie' - Dig this! Things along 'Deep Wylie' are going to get 'boring' and 'more boring' for the guys and dolls who frequent 'Pittsburgh's highway of hilarity' within the new year, as this piece of boring equipment at work at the corner of Wylie and Logan Street indicates.  Eventually, instead of the 'cats' digging this main Hill District traffic artery for 'high life' it will be bulldozers digging it for the high-lifts.  It's the beginning of the end. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Intersection of Wylie Avenue and Logan Street with Gilbert's Billiards on left and large boring machine on sidewalk, in preparation of razing the neighborhood, Lower Hill District
